# Example of a complex relationship chain:
# A TroubleTicket (TT-20240420-001) is related to a Service (CorporateDNS) and Resources (DNS01, RouterCore01).
# It was triggered by EventRecords (DNSOutageLog01, RouterInterfaceDown).
# The EventRecords originated from specific ManagedObjects (DNS01, RouterCore01) and a ManagementSystem (MonitoringPlatform).
# A TroubleTicketNote (TT-20240420-001-Note2) is part of the TroubleTicket and correlates to an EventRecord (RouterInterfaceDown).
# An OperationPlan (RestartDNSService) is proposed for an alarm (DNSOutageLog01).
# A ChangeRequest (CR-20240419-001) impacts a Resource (RouterCore01) and a Service (InternetAccessService).
# The RouterCore01 is located at a Locus (RackA2) in a Room (ServerRoomA) in a Site (DataCenterParis).
# The RouterCore01 has NetworkInterfaces (RouterCore01-Ge0_0_0, RouterCore01-Ge0_0_1) which connect to NetworkLinks (ISP-CoreRouterLink, CoreRouter-SwitchUplink).
# The RouterCore01 is managed by the NetworkAdminTeam (foaf:Agent/NetworkAdminTeam).
# The NetworkAdminTeam also manages the CorporateDNS application.
# The CorporateDNS application has a module (CorporateDNS-Prod) which is in production.
# The CorporateDNS application uses the DNS01 resource.
# The DNS01 resource has a network interface (DNS01-Eth0) connected to a network link (DNS01-SwitchLink).
# The DNS01-SwitchLink connects to the SwitchAccess01.
# The SwitchAccess01 is also managed by the NetworkAdminTeam.
# The SwitchAccess01 has an uplink to the CoreRouter01 via CoreRouter-SwitchUplink.
# This demonstrates a dense and interconnected graph.
